Letter to the Editor: Recovery and outcomes of patients denied early liver transplantation for severe alcohol-associated hepatitis.
The article's main point is that spontaneous recovery from alcoholic hepatitis following liver transplant evaluation is associated with younger age, a lower international normalized ratio (INR) index, and a lower peak model for end-stage liver disease (MELD) scores. Relapse to alcohol use is the most common cause of impaired post-recovery survival;  however, among al alcoholic hepatitis survivors, only liver transplantation was associated with improved survival. However, it seemed worthwhile to add a few more points to improve the article's conclusion.
