 POP is technically successful in the vast majority of patients with (suspected) IPMN, has a considerably high diagnostic accuracy, but an adverse event rate of 12%. Data on intraoperative pancreatoscopy is scarce, but small studies suggest its use can alter surgical management. Future studies are needed to better define the role of POP in the diagnostic work-up of IPMN.
