    Normative values for esophageal functional lumen imaging probe measurements: A meta-analysis.
Given these observations, we recommend using a cut-off of 2mm 2 /mmHg for clinical practice, values below can be considered abnormal. Given that 5.4% of the healthy subjects will have an EGJ-DI below 2mm 2 /mmHg at 40ml, we recommend using the 50 and 60ml distention volumes. The clinical use of an upper limit for normality of EGJ-DI seems questionable.
